Robert Singer is an American television producer , director and writer .
He is best known for his work on Supernatural where he serves as an executive producer , director and occasional writer .
The character Bobby Singer was named after him .
A fictionalized version of Singer appears in the season 6 episode The French Mistake played by Brian Doyle-Murray .
Singer also created the series Reasonable Doubts and has worked as a producer and director on various television series , including Lois & Clark : The New Adventures of Superman .
He also served as a producer for the film Cujo